{"cursor":"6444","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n automobile.]]\n\n'Snow chains', or 'tire chains', are devices fitted to the tires of vehicles to\nprovide maximum traction when driving through snow and ice.\n\nSnow chains are attached to the drive wheels of a vehicle. Chains are usually\nsold in pairs and must be purchased to match a particular tire size (tire\ndiameter and tread width). Driving with chains reduces fuel efficiency and can\nreduce the speed of the automobile to approximately 50 km/h (30 mph).\n","linknr":161,"url":"Snow_chains","recorded":1362476869,"links":38,"instances":[],"pdf":["http://www.witruck.org/state_chain_laws.pdf"],"categories":["Chains","Automotive safety technologies","Inclement weather management"],"headings":["Deployment","United States","Common chain failures","Varieties and alternatives","Legality of use","External links","Notes"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Ambox_globe_content.svg/48px-Ambox_globe_content.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cc/Snow_Chain_Honda.jpg/220px-Snow_Chain_Honda.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/City_bus_with_tire_chains%2C_TriMet_%28Oregon%29_in_2008.jpg/220px-City_bus_with_tire_chains%2C_TriMet_%28Oregon%29_in_2008.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Tire_chain_for_motorcycle.jpg/220px-Tire_chain_for_motorcycle.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Cable_chains_on_bus%2C_TriMet_%28Oregon%29_2008.jpg/220px-Cable_chains_on_bus%2C_TriMet_%28Oregon%29_2008.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upl